<section class="page" id="page-__BW_MERGE_PAGE__" data-page-key="merge" data-page-relevance="reviewer designer pm">
  <span class="eyebrow">Page 8 · Merge plan</span>
  <h1 class="display display-l" style="margin: 16px 0 0;">Recommended integration sequence</h1>
  <p class="lead" style="margin-top: 24px;">
    Two trees, one external dependency. Tree A merges in fork order behind the
    <code>sdk-swift 2.0.0-6370-96753eef</code> release; Tree B merges independently.
  </p>

  <ol class="step-list" style="margin-top: 48px;">
    <li class="step-item">
      <div class="step-num"></div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3>#2573 — Bank Account foundation (PM-32809)</h3>
        <p>Foundation types, feature flag, icon. No SDK dependency. <strong>Merge first.</strong></p>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li class="step-item">
      <div class="step-num"></div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3>#2576 — Bank Account SDK bridge (PM-32809)</h3>
        <p>Adds <code>CipherType.bankAccount</code> + SDK bridge arms. <strong>Held</strong> until
          <code class="mono">sdk-swift 2.0.0-6370-96753eef</code> publishes.</p>
        <div class="step-zone">↳ Blocker: SDK release. Cannot merge until the bridge symbol exists in published SDK.</div>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li class="step-item">
      <div class="step-num"></div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3>#2577 + #2578 — Driver's License & Passport (PM-32807, PM-32805)</h3>
        <p>Sibling parsers off the #2576 fork. Merge in either order once #2576 lands; both share the same
          SDK hold. Expect mechanical conflict in <code class="mono">CipherType.swift</code> /
          <code class="mono">CipherTypeTests.swift</code> / <code class="mono">BitwardenSdk+Vault.swift</code> —
          accept both new arms.</p>
        <div class="step-zone">↳ Whichever lands second: re-add its <code>CipherType</code> case + bridge arm + parser entry.</div>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li class="step-item">
      <div class="step-num"></div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3>#2582 — Promote ExpandableHeaderView (PM-35398)</h3>
        <p>Independent of Tree A. Self-flagged Authenticator visual drift (token swaps). Awaiting design /
          product input on the open question; can merge in parallel with Tree A as soon as that resolves.</p>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li class="step-item">
      <div class="step-num"></div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3>#2583 — Binding&lt;Bool&gt; initializer (PM-35398)</h3>
        <p>Builds on #2582. Lands the caller-owned expansion-state initializer. Vault-list section headers
          (BWPM) consume this in a later PR.</p>
      </div>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h2 class="section-heading" style="margin-top: 64px;">Open items <span class="section-count">stitching pending</span></h2>
  <div class="finding-card finding-card-q">
    <div class="finding-head">
      <span class="finding-sev">Question</span>
      <span class="finding-title">Authenticator visual drift on #2582</span>
      <span class="triage-status badge-question" style="margin-left: auto;">Seeded</span>
    </div>
    <div class="finding-body">
      Self-flagged in the PR body. Three token swaps land different Authenticator visuals
      (<code>textSecondary</code>, <code>backgroundPrimary</code>, <code>accessoryIcon → accessoryIcon16</code>).
      Pre-seeded as a stakeholder question on the cover; tagged <em>design</em> + <em>product</em>. See PR #2582 page
      for the full drift table and surrounding context.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="finding-card">
    <div class="finding-head">
      <span class="finding-sev">Pending</span>
      <span class="finding-title">Per-PR review verdicts</span>
    </div>
    <div class="finding-body">
      Six per-PR reviews are running in parallel. As each completes, its
      <code>verdict</code> field in <code>data.js</code> will be flipped from <code>pending</code> to
      its real value (<code>approve</code> / <code>approve-fix</code> / <code>block</code>) and the
      cover Verdicts table will populate. No code change needed in <code>app.js</code> for the swap.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="decision-widget">
    <h3 class="decision-title">Final disposition</h3>
    <p class="decision-sub">Use the running tally above each page; this is space for an overall note.</p>
